lemma IsAltPath.of_cons (h : G.IsAltPath hM (.cons x e P)) : G.IsAltPath hM P := by
  simp only [isAltPath_iff, cons_isPath_iff, WList.cons_edge] at h ⊢
  obtain ⟨⟨hP, hl, hx⟩, he⟩ := h
  exact ⟨hP, he.of_cons⟩
```

This lemma shows that if $P$ is an alternating path starting with $x$ and edge $e$, then the rest of the path $P$ is also an alternating path. This is straightforward because the definition of an alternating path is preserved by removing the first edge.

