  match P with
  | .nil u => simp_all
  | .cons u e w => simp [h.of_cons]
```

This lemma shows that if $P$ is an alternating path, then $P$ is also an alternating path when considered as a path starting from the second vertex. This is true because the definition of an alternating path is preserved by taking the tail.

