    List.IsChain.singleton, Option.mem_def, List.head?_cons, Option.some.injEq, forall_eq',
    true_and] at h ⊢
  obtain ⟨⟨hP, hl, hx⟩, he, hlast⟩ := h
  refine ⟨hP, he⟩
```

This lemma shows that if $P$ is an alternating path formed by concatenating two paths, then the first path is also an alternating path. This is true because the definition of an alternating path is preserved under concatenation.

