  obtain ⟨v, rfl⟩ | hne := P.exists_eq_nil_or_nonempty
  · rwa [WList.dropLast_nil]
  obtain ⟨w', f, y, rfl⟩ := hne.exists_concat
  rw [WList.dropLast_concat]
  exact h.of_concat
```

This lemma shows that if $P$ is an alternating path, then $P$ is also an alternating path when considered as a path without the last vertex. This is true because the definition of an alternating path is preserved under removing the last vertex.

