This lemma shows that the set of vertices matched by $M$ is a subset of the vertices matched by the new matching $M \Delta E(P)$. This is true because the augmenting path $P$ has endpoints that are unmatched by $M$, so they become matched in $M \Delta E(P)$, and all other vertices along the path were already matched by $M$ or remain matched in $M \Delta E(P)$.

